explanation: This solution uses bitwise operations to efficiently count the set bits in the binary representation of the input integer. The bitwise AND operation (n & 1) checks if the least significant bit is set, and the bitwise right shift operation (n >>= 1) shifts the bits to the right. The loop continues until all bits have been processed, resulting in a time complexity of O(log n).

